  "original_title": "Imithiaz calls out President on his duplicity concerning the \u2018Aragalaya\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Imithiaz calls out President on his duplicity concerning the \u2018Aragalaya\u2019",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) MP Imthiaz Bakeer Markar has called out President Ranil Wickremesinghe on his duplicity relating to the Aragalaya and its peaceful protestors. \u201cOnce he was appointed, he created a sense of hope by claiming he was not against the citizen\u2019s struggle. He even promised to appoint a committee to look into their needs and not repress the people\u2019s right to protest peacefully.",
        "\u201cHe included a politician, the Municipal Council and even the Police into the Committee and claimed all necessary facilities to continue the struggle will be provided,\u201d Markar said. \u201cHe said this in words but he is doing something drastically different through his actions today,\u201d Makar pointed out.",
        "The MP made these comments during a press conference held by the SJB in Colombo yesterday.",
        "\u201cIf he was truly a democratic leader he would have not signed these detention orders under the Prevention of Terrorism Act and allowed for the arrests of innocent and peaceful students activists under a law that is meant for those carrying out crimes against the State,\u201d Markar said.",
        "\u201cThere is a great contradiction between what was said and what is being done today,\u201d he noted. According to Markar, the President is attempting to deceive the people. Markar called on the people to not fall for the fairy tales spun by Wickremesinghe. \u201cWe will have to answer to the International Human Rights Organisations in the end,\u201d he said.",
        "\u201cThis will not only be a threat to the country\u2019s democracy but it will also threaten our economic state. The country was severely affected by the loss of the GSP+ concession. Where are we heading now? None of the criticisms against the country by international organisations is being reported in the media,\u201d he said.",
        "Markar accused a possible cat\u2019s paw of influencing the media. \u201cHead of media organisations, swimming champions, student\u2019s activists and others are being summoned to the CID. What is the aim of these actions? The message is that the Government is ready to hunt anyone opposing them or attempting to obstruct the revival of those who caused this economic collapse. The people must understand this. Repression of those opposing the Government cannot take place without the blessings of the President,\u201d Markar added."
      ],
